data.name: metroLabel3.Text
data.value: The usage is simple. 1. First of all, you should create an empty file or import problem from the existing files(*.xml). 2. Then change to the "Edit Problem" tab to modify the problem description and limits. Adding or altering data test case in "Add Data" tab. 3. Last, do not forget to save your change. Beside, there are some options in "Settings" tab. Read the manual for more informations.

data.name: metroLabel2.Text
data.value: ProblemSetter is a tool that used to create the problem file(*.xml which including problem description and test data). Also, you can use it to import existing problem file(*.xml) and then modify it as well as add some test data if you want.
